a.xlink:title: Chains Is used to map addresses to a chain. Chain_id (PK) is based on the chain's id (see chainlist).
Addresses Represents wallet and smart contract addresses, linked to chains, projects, and categorization.
Projects Information about specific projects (i.e. Uniswap V2), including project name, website link, and documentation.
Categories A classification system that can be used for grouping contracts and wallets into specific categories.
TagMapping A many-to-many relationship table that maps tags to addresses, allowing an address to have multiple tags and a tag to be applied to multiple addresses.
Team A group of people or entities working on projects, with a simple structure containing just an ID and a name.
MainCategories A higher-level categorization that can group multiple categories under a broader classification.
TagGroup Represents collections of tags that can be applied to other entities in the system for organizational purposes.
Tags Individual labels or identifiers that can be applied to data points for sorting, searching, and categorization purposes.
